flowchart TB
    User[kubectl / CI-CD Pipeline] -->|1. Submit YAML| APIServer[kube-apiserver]

    subgraph AdmissionWebhooks ["Admission Control Webhooks"]
        WebhookSvc[Operator Webhook Server]
        APIServer -->|2. Mutating Request| WebhookSvc
        WebhookSvc -->|Inject defaults| APIServer
        APIServer -->|3. Validating Request| WebhookSvc
        WebhookSvc -->|Reject invalid schema/drift| APIServer
    end

    subgraph HighAvailability ["Operator Pods (HA Lock)"]
        PodLeader[Operator Pod A\n(Active Leader)]
        PodReplica[Operator Pod B\n(Standby)]
        
        LeaderElection[Coordination Lease Lock\n'postgres-operator-lock']
        
        PodLeader -->|Maintain Lease| LeaderElection
        PodReplica -.->|Try acquire Lease| LeaderElection
    end

    subgraph Monitoring ["Metrics & Telemetry"]
        Prometheus[Prometheus Server]
        MetricsPort[Operator Metrics Endpoint /metrics]
        
        Prometheus -->|Scrape metrics| MetricsPort
        PodLeader -->|Export stats: reconciliation_latency, resource_count| MetricsPort
    end

    APIServer -->|4. Watch updates| PodLeader
    PodLeader -->|5. Reconcile Stateful Sets| StatefulSets[Database StatefulSets]

    classDef core fill:#0f172a,stroke:#38bdf8,color:#fff;
    classDef webhook fill:#581c87,stroke:#c084fc,color:#fff;
    classDef ha fill:#064e3b,stroke:#34d399,color:#fff;
    classDef monitor fill:#7c2d12,stroke:#f97316,color:#fff;

    class User,APIServer,StatefulSets core;
    class WebhookSvc webhook;
    class PodLeader,PodReplica,LeaderElection ha;
    class Prometheus,MetricsPort monitor;
